John Ross COOPER v. Fred G. ZERBST Warden of the United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 1093. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. May 15, 1934. Walter T. Chaney, of Topeka, Kan., for appellant. S. S. Alexander, U. S. Atty., of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

. Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for want of merit.
